name: Last Flicker #04
description: Once ubiquitous, the neon signs of the Hong Kong's streetscape are rapidly disappearing. I capture these iconic giants before they are gone. Getting up close - and even inside these iconic installations, you can feel the buzz of electricity and flicker of failing neon. Several of the signs captured in this series have already been dismantled. This edition of 500 has been minted for the #OBJKT4OBJKT swap weekend.
